Calculator Project
Overview
This is a simple web-based calculator built with HTML, CSS, and JavaScript. The calculator supports basic arithmetic operations like addition, subtraction, multiplication, and division.

Features
Basic Arithmetic: Perform addition, subtraction, multiplication, and division.
Responsive Design: The calculator is styled to look good on both desktop and mobile devices.
Clear Input: A clear button is available to reset the input field.
Multiple Operations: The calculator allows chaining operations with proper order of execution.
Technologies Used
HTML5: Structure of the calculator interface.
CSS3: Styling and layout for a better user experience.
JavaScript: Core functionality for performing calculations and handling user input.
Installation
Clone the Repository:
bash
Copy code
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/calculator-project.git

Launch the Calculator:
Use the number buttons to enter your desired numbers.
Click the operation buttons (e.g., +, -, *, /) to choose the operation.
Click the = button to get the result.
Use the C button to clear the input field.
Code Explanation
JavaScript Functions:
SetN(operator): Sets the current operation.
calculate(): Computes the result based on the selected operation.
clearNum(): Clears the input field.
Number functions (e.g., seven(), eight()): Append the respective number to the input field.
clearFlag: Used to manage when the input field should be cleared (e.g., after a result is displayed).